You are an expert resume writer. Write a concise mission statement (15-30 words,
max 200 characters) for the top of a resume targeting the following role.

## Target Role

{{ jd_analysis.role_title }} at {{ jd_analysis.company }}
Seniority: {{ jd_analysis.seniority_level }}
Summary: {{ jd_analysis.role_summary }}

## Themes to Incorporate

{% for theme in mission_themes %}
- {{ theme }}
{% endfor %}

## Guidelines

The mission statement is NOT an objective ("Seeking a role in..."). It is a
positioning statement that tells the reader who this candidate is in 1 sentence.

Formula: "[descriptor] [role-type] with [X years] experience in [core domain],
specializing in [what matters to this JD]."

Good examples:
- "Staff engineer with 12 years building high-throughput distributed systems, specializing in platform reliability and developer productivity."
- "Full-stack engineer with deep expertise in React and Node.js, focused on shipping accessible, performant web applications at scale."

Bad examples (do NOT write like this):
- "Passionate software engineer seeking new opportunities..." (objective, not positioning)
- "Experienced professional with a proven track record..." (vague, buzzwordy)

Respond with a JSON object containing:
- `text`: The mission statement (max 200 chars)
- `rationale`: One sentence on why this framing works for this specific application
